Hint  Use *man* if you can't guess how it might work.   Answer <pre><code>$ cd ~/test
$ cat hello.c
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;
int main(void) {
    printf ("Hello World\n");
    return 0;
}
</code></pre>  *hello.c* contains the source code of a C program. The compiled executable version of this code is in the file called *hi*, which you can run like so:  <pre><code>$ ./hi
Hello World
</code></pre>
